Finally, although doxorubicin showed strong antiproliferative activity
against all tested cancer cell lines, it is important to emphasize
its high cytotoxicity toward HaCaT cells (Table 
). In all cases, the SI values of doxorubicin
were lower than 1.0, indicating that the compound preferentially targets
healthy cells over cancerous ones (Table 
). In contrast, almost all bioconjugates
displayed SI values greater than 1.0, underscoring their high anticancer
potential (Table 
).
